cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper deals with robot learning and policy search, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions simulation results, which suggests that it may fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as well. Finally, the paper proposes a factorization approach to contextual policy search, which involves modeling the environment and task objectives separately, which could be relevant to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
